><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">Transfer cells to a 15 ml centrifuge tube. Pellet cells by centrifugation at 4500 xg for 5 min at <\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"> <\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">.<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">Carefully remove supernatant by pipetting. Be cautious not to perturb the pellet, to avoid loosing material.<\/li><\/ul><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Transfer cells to a 15 ml centrifuge tube. Pellet cells by centrifugation at 4500 xg for 5 min at <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><ul style = \"list-style-type:disc;\"><\/ul><\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"06C99DC0133D11E98FD037159407B782","order_id":2,"type_id":24,"title":"temperature","source":{"concentration":12,"unit":"\u00b0C","title":""}},{"id":1054726,"guid":"1CAC2F90133D11E98FD037159407B782","order_id":3,"type_id":4,"title":"duration","source":{"duration":480,"title":""}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF"},{"id":694205,"guid":"E926F3A00E9911E9BB2E0DD05BB2BDCF","previous_id":694201,"previous_guid":"F5C602100E8311E9BB2E0DD05BB2BDCF","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"79C90E5DAD2E4A168649A4C38A98B94F","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Lyse cells and extract total RNA"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"F63F86E0F996459EADB004531454A987","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Resuspend the cell pellet with <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> of TRIzol (ThermoFisher Scientific) by gently pipetting up and down, until the pellet is completely dissolved. Incubate suspension for 5 min at room temperature.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><ul style = \"list-style-type:disc;\"><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">Transfer the TRIzol-suspended material to a new 1.5 ml microcentrifuge tube with safe lock (Eppendorf).<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">Freeze the suspension by submerging the tube in liquid nitrogen. Once it is completely freezed (nitrogen stops boiling), transfer the tube to a thermal block pre-warmed at 50 \u00b0C  and taw the solution for 5 min.<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">Repeat freeze-tawing cycle once.<\/li><\/ul><\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"60B735500E9B11E9BB2E0DD05BB2BDCF","order_id":2,"type_id":3,"title":"amount","source":{"amount":1,"unit":"ml","title":""}},{"id":1054726,"guid":"D62B95230CAA4AF5AA040B8936F4D3B3","order_id":3,"type_id":26,"title":"notes","source":{"id":0,"parent_id":0,"uri":"","title":"","body":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Make sure that no pellet remaining is visible at the bottom of the tube after resuspension. See manufacturer's protocol for more details on using this reagent.<\/div><\/div>","created_on":0,"changed_on":0,"creator":{"name":" ","affiliation":"","username":"","link":null,"image":{"source":"","placeholder":""},"badges":[],"research_interests":null},"comments":[]}},{"id":1054727,"guid":"D623529A06E14D1DB71F5149C768CFB0","order_id":4,"type_id":26,"title":"notes","source":{"id":0,"parent_id":0,"uri":"","title":"","body":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">STOPPING POINT:<\/span><span> TRIzol suspensions can be kept at <\/span><a style = \"text-decoration:underline;color:blue;cursor:pointer;\"><span style = \":;\"> <\/span><\/a><span> for up to 2 weeks or at <\/span><a style = \"text-decoration:underline;color:blue;cursor:pointer;\"><span style = \":;\"> <\/span><\/a><span> for long-term storage.<\/span><\/div><\/div>","created_on":0,"changed_on":0,"creator":{"name":" ","affiliation":"","username":"","link":null,"image":{"source":"","placeholder":""},"badges":[],"research_interests":null},"comments":[]}},{"id":1054728,"guid":"D30D91A0133F11E98FD037159407B782","order_id":5,"type_id":4,"title":"duration","source":{"duration":1500,"title":""}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#EA94FF"},{"id":694210,"guid":"72EC5A100E9C11E9BB2E0DD05BB2BDCF","previous_id":694205,"previous_guid":"E926F3A00E9911E9BB2E0DD05BB2BDCF","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"EB6A4439DE1747D8B76113BDFB9C0C10","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Separate phases and isolate RNA"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"FBC475A4D26741D28AE6534B31B4FD95","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Add <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">of 1-bromo-3-chloropropane (Sigma-Aldrich). Cap the tube and seal it with parafilm to avoid leaks. <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><ul style = \"list-style-type:disc;\"><\/ul><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Centrifuge at 12,000 xg for 15 min at <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Transfer the aqueous (superior) phase containing RNA (aproximately <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">) to a clean, new 1.5 mL tube.\n<\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"888993900E9E11E9BB2E0DD05BB2BDCF","order_id":2,"type_id":3,"title":"amount","source":{"amount":100,"unit":"\u00b5l","title":""}},{"id":1054726,"guid":"F3A6543971AE4043A4906B80A288D74A","order_id":3,"type_id":26,"title":"notes","source":{"id":0,"parent_id":0,"uri":"","title":"","body":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">1-Br-3-Cl-propane<\/span><span> performs better than <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">chloroform<\/span><span> for phase separation helping to avoid gDNA contamination (interphase is more \u2018compact\u2019 after centrifugation).<\/span><\/div><\/div>","created_on":0,"changed_on":0,"creator":{"name":" ","affiliation":"","username":"","link":null,"image":{"source":"","placeholder":""},"badges":[],"research_interests":null},"comments":[]}},{"id":1054727,"guid":"25C39480134011E98FD037159407B782","order_id":4,"type_id":24,"title":"temperature","source":{"concentration":4,"unit":"\u00b0C","title":""}},{"id":1054728,"guid":"3B623F80134011E98FD037159407B782","order_id":5,"type_id":3,"title":"amount","source":{"amount":600,"unit":"\u00b5l","title":""}},{"id":1054729,"guid":"C3D1F3A230C9485A9AAEF3FAE9A2F16A","order_id":6,"type_id":26,"title":"notes","source":{"id":0,"parent_id":0,"uri":"","title":"","body":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Interphase contains genomic DNA. So, be careful while pipetting to avoid DNA contamination in the RNA sample. Lower phase contain proteins.<\/div><\/div>","created_on":0,"changed_on":0,"creator":{"name":" ","affiliation":"","username":"","link":null,"image":{"source":"","placeholder":""},"badges":[],"research_interests":null},"comments":[]}},{"id":1054730,"guid":"4EAA5050134011E98FD037159407B782","order_id":7,"type_id":4,"title":"duration","source":{"duration":1800,"title":""}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#94EBFF"},{"id":694214,"guid":"22137ED00EA011E9BB2E0DD05BB2BDCF","previous_id":694210,"previous_guid":"72EC5A100E9C11E9BB2E0DD05BB2BDCF","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"B335EFFEFEA64CBABCA2C94ACE9583CD","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Precipitate RNA"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"278E9B3F5C354471B689854F6E2D8660","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Add <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">of isopropanol. Invert 3-4 times to mix and incubate 15 min at room temperature.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Centrifuge at 12,000 xg for 10 min at <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Discard supernatant and add 1 ml of 75% ethanol (freshly prepared), vortex briefly and centrifuge at 8,500 xg for 5 min at <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><ul style = \"list-style-type:disc;\"><\/ul><\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"42E54A300EA011E9BB2E0DD05BB2BDCF","order_id":2,"type_id":3,"title":"amount","source":{"amount":500,"unit":"\u00b5l","title":""}},{"id":1054726,"guid":"8B8E1510134011E98FD037159407B782","order_id":3,"type_id":24,"title":"temperature","source":{"concentration":4,"unit":"\u00b0C","title":""}},{"id":1054727,"guid":"B806F850134011E98FD037159407B782","order_id":4,"type_id":24,"title":"temperature","source":{"concentration":4,"unit":"\u00b0C","title":""}},{"id":1054728,"guid":"AB261D7DC4634349806F68A11D815185","order_id":5,"type_id":26,"title":"notes","source":{"id":0,"parent_id":0,"uri":"","title":"","body":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">CRITICAL!<\/span><span>: Avoid overdrying, as it will make RNA very difficult to resuspend.<\/span><\/div><\/div>","created_on":0,"changed_on":0,"creator":{"name":" ","affiliation":"","username":"","link":null,"image":{"source":"","placeholder":""},"badges":[],"research_interests":null},"comments":[]}},{"id":1054729,"guid":"E0E528A0134011E98FD037159407B782","order_id":6,"type_id":4,"title":"duration","source":{"duration":2400,"title":""}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#FFED92"},{"id":694218,"guid":"12A382A00EA111E9BB2E0DD05BB2BDCF","previous_id":694214,"previous_guid":"22137ED00EA011E9BB2E0DD05BB2BDCF","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"AF76DE0BC8F34774BF66BC368E0C2B6A","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Resuspend RNA"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"23B40ADA81A84BA98AA56C022BF78B25","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Add <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> of nuclease-free water, and resuspend by gently pipetting while heating at <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">. Spin down to collect the whole volume at the bottom of the tube.<\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"32AD43100EA111E9BB2E0DD05BB2BDCF","order_id":2,"type_id":3,"title":"amount","source":{"amount":30,"unit":"\u00b5l","title":""}},{"id":1054726,"guid":"3AB2CA300EA111E9BB2E0DD05BB2BDCF","order_id":3,"type_id":24,"title":"temperature","source":{"concentration":56,"unit":"\u00b0C","title":""}},{"id":1054727,"guid":"75289D86182C4090B53792FDE996E6A0","order_id":4,"type_id":26,"title":"notes","source":{"id":0,"parent_id":0,"uri":"","title":"","body":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Water volume can be adjusted as needed. Tipically 30 to 50 uL are used.<\/div><\/div>","created_on":0,"changed_on":0,"creator":{"name":" ","affiliation":"","username":"","link":null,"image":{"source":"","placeholder":""},"badges":[],"research_interests":null},"comments":[]}},{"id":1054728,"guid":"FB173E70134011E98FD037159407B782","order_id":5,"type_id":4,"title":"duration","source":{"duration":300,"title":""}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#EA9F6C"},{"id":694220,"guid":"85A509E00EA111E9BB2E0DD05BB2BDCF","previous_id":694218,"previous_guid":"12A382A00EA111E9BB2E0DD05BB2BDCF","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"FE39FEA151EA42E6BF969DBA3797AF5F","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Measure RNA concentration"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"12E6C2D051C04DFFBB8DD2816D74ED2B","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"> Measure RNA concentration by spectrophotometry (for example, using nanodrop instrument).<\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"008578E0134111E98FD037159407B782","order_id":2,"type_id":4,"title":"duration","source":{"duration":120,"title":""}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#E57785"},{"id":695232,"guid":"D8D528F0133A11E98FD037159407B782","previous_id":694220,"previous_guid":"85A509E00EA111E9BB2E0DD05BB2BDCF","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"841664F637A84F58950F55D98F0522E1","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"DNAse I treatement"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"94F7B1FF0345470F97109A3715E00E77","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Transfer up to 10 \u00b5g of total RNA to a clean, new tube. Complete volume with nuclease-free water to reach a final volume of 40.5 \u00b5l and then add:<\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><ul style = \"list-style-type:disc;\"><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">5 \u00b5l 10X DNAseI buffer (Thermofisher)<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">2 \u00b5l RNAseOUT (Thermofisher)<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">5 \u00b5l DNAseI (Thermofisher)<\/li><\/ul><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Incubate at room temperature for 15 min and inactivate the reaction by adding 1 \u00b5l EDTA solution and incubating for 10 min at <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">.<\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"6BF9CF90133C11E98FD037159407B782","order_id":2,"type_id":24,"title":"temperature","source":{"concentration":65,"unit":"\u00b0C","title":""}},{"id":1054726,"guid":"BD7FDDF0133C11E98FD037159407B782","order_id":3,"type_id":4,"title":"duration","source":{"duration":1200,"title":""}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF"},{"id":695234,"guid":"7E806520133C11E98FD037159407B782","previous_id":695232,"previous_guid":"D8D528F0133A11E98FD037159407B782","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"377B8EAC984D4D5E99F1C00B58A7F62B","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"RNA precipitation"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"7E0D8CC58204410CAAEDCFF8E444C0C1","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Add 5 \u00b5l of 5M LiCl plus two volumes (110 \u00b5l) of 100% ethanol, previously cooled at <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">. Precipitate overnight at <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">NEXT DAY:<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Centrifuge at maximum speed for 15 min at <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">. Discard supernatant carefully with pipette.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Wash once with 1 ml 70% ethanol (cold at <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">).<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Centrifuge at maximum speed for 5 min at <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">, discard supernatant and dry at room temperature for 10-15 min.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Resuspend pellet (sometimes not visible) with 20 \u00b5l of nuclease-free water, by pipetting up and down. Flick the tube, spin down, and incubate overnight at <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> for complete resuspension.<\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"A9791100133C11E98FD037159407B782","order_id":2,"type_id":24,"title":"temperature","source":{"concentration":-20,"unit":"\u00b0C","title":""}},{"id":1054726,"guid":"C64580C0133C11E98FD037159407B782","order_id":3,"type_id":24,"title":"temperature","source":{"concentration":-80,"unit":"\u00b0C","title":""}},{"id":1054727,"guid":"6A8DF140134111E98FD037159407B782","order_id":4,"type_id":24,"title":"temperature","source":{"concentration":4,"unit":"\u00b0C","title":""}},{"id":1054728,"guid":"8606B7E0134111E98FD037159407B782","order_id":5,"type_id":24,"title":"temperature","source":{"concentration":-20,"unit":"\u00b0C","title":""}},{"id":1054729,"guid":"94F8B500134111E98FD037159407B782","order_id":6,"type_id":24,"title":"temperature","source":{"concentration":4,"unit":"\u00b0C","title":""}},{"id":1054730,"guid":"2BDA89C075D1437D9EFCC574BCED0003","order_id":7,"type_id":26,"title":"notes","source":{"id":0,"parent_id":0,"uri":"","title":"","body":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">CRITICAL!:<\/span><span> Be extremelly careful not to overdry the sample. Dry RNA is very difficult to resuspend.<\/span><\/div><\/div>","created_on":0,"changed_on":0,"creator":{"name":" ","affiliation":"","username":"","link":null,"image":{"source":"","placeholder":""},"badges":[],"research_interests":null},"comments":[]}},{"id":1054731,"guid":"EF635FE0134111E98FD037159407B782","order_id":8,"type_id":24,"title":"temperature","source":{"concentration":-80,"unit":"\u00b0C","title":""}},{"id":1054732,"guid":"1D967640134211E98FD037159407B782","order_id":9,"type_id":4,"title":"duration","source":{"duration":172800,"title":"(Includes two overnight incubations.)"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#94EBFF"},{"id":695236,"guid":"DC3C5DE0133C11E98FD037159407B782","previous_id":695234,"previous_guid":"7E806520133C11E98FD037159407B782","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"502CE4C77FAF4DF7B1AA77EF267718A1","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Measure RNA concentration"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"2AB09F309BED4FA1937A794B4296630C","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Measure RNA concentration by spectrophotometry (for example, using nanodrop instrument).<\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"899BE100134B11E98FD037159407B782","order_id":2,"type_id":4,"title":"duration","source":{"duration":120,"title":""}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#FFED92"},{"id":695247,"guid":"DDB13BE0134211E98FD037159407B782","previous_id":695236,"previous_guid":"DC3C5DE0133C11E98FD037159407B782","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"86CB9353D7D743C9BA647903E2D1C86A","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"cDNA synthesis"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"BE1D981CB24B4BABAE8AA042247F4761","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><ul style = \"list-style-type:disc;\"><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">Calculate the appropriate volume of DNAse-treated total RNA for 0.5 to 3 \u00b5g of RNA. Volume should not exceed 8 \u00b5l. Assemble the following reaction preferably in DNA LoBind 0.5 \u00b5l tubes (Eppendorf).<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"> <\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">            Total RNA ------------------------- x \u00b5l<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">            Nuclease-free water --------- 8 - x \u00b5l<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">            oligo dT primer ----------------- 1\u00b5l<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">            10X dNTP mix ------------------ 1\u00b5l<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">On thermocycler, heat the mix for 5 min at <\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"> <\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">, then cool down immediately on ice.<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">While on ice, add 10 \u00b5l of cDNA reaction mix of the following composition:<\/li><\/ul><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">            Total RNA ------------------------- x \u00b5l<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">            Nuclease-free water --------- 8 - x \u00b5l<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">            oligo dT primer ----------------- 1\u00b5l<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">            10X dNTP mix ------------------ 1\u00b5l<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">On thermocycler, heat the mix for 5 min at <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">, then cool down immediately on ice.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><ul style = \"list-style-type:disc;\"><\/ul><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">            10X Superscript III buffer ----- 2 \u00b5l<\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span>            25 mM MgCl<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">2 <\/span><span>---------------------- 4 \u00b5l<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">            0.1 M DTT ---------------------------- 2 \u00b5l<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">            RNAseOUT -------------------------- 1 \u00b5l<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">            Superscript III ---------------------- 1 \u00b5l<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Homogenize the mixture, quickly spin down and immediately incubate for 75 min at <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">, followed by 5 min incubation at <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">to inactivate the enzyme.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Treat samples with 1 \u00b5l RNAse H (provided with the SuperScript kit), for 1 hour at <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> (in a water bath).<\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"3811A3BCD98D4C47935BA8ADB3A98F8A","order_id":2,"type_id":26,"title":"notes","source":{"id":0,"parent_id":0,"uri":"","title":"","body":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">If DNA LoBind tubes are not available, use normal PCR tubes.<\/div><\/div>","created_on":0,"changed_on":0,"creator":{"name":" ","affiliation":"","username":"","link":null,"image":{"source":"","placeholder":""},"badges":[],"research_interests":null},"comments":[]}},{"id":1054726,"guid":"7E1020B0134811E98FD037159407B782","order_id":3,"type_id":24,"title":"temperature","source":{"concentration":65,"unit":"\u00b0C","title":""}},{"id":1054727,"guid":"BA763480134911E98FD037159407B782","order_id":4,"type_id":24,"title":"temperature","source":{"concentration":50,"unit":"\u00b0C","title":""}},{"id":1054728,"guid":"EC8A2E90134911E98FD037159407B782","order_id":5,"type_id":24,"title":"temperature","source":{"concentration":85,"unit":"\u00b0C","title":""}},{"id":1054729,"guid":"093B9C40134A11E98FD037159407B782","order_id":6,"type_id":24,"title":"temperature","source":{"concentration":37,"unit":"\u00b0C","title":""}},{"id":1054730,"guid":"0A1B92AF977D4AC584D535B655179064","order_id":7,"type_id":26,"title":"notes","source":{"id":0,"parent_id":0,"uri":"","title":"","body":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Reagents used in this step are from SuperScript III First Strand Synthesis Kit (Invitrogen).<\/div><\/div>","created_on":0,"changed_on":0,"creator":{"name":" ","affiliation":"","username":"","link":null,"image":{"source":"","placeholder":""},"badges":[],"research_interests":null},"comments":[]}},{"id":1054731,"guid":"A17587E0134B11E98FD037159407B782","order_id":8,"type_id":4,"title":"duration","source":{"duration":9000,"title":""}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#EA9F6C"}],"materials":[],"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><div class = \"justify\" style = \"text-align:justify\"><span>This protocol describes the steps for isolation of total RNA for cDNA synthesis in the marine Ichthyosporean <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">Sphaeroforma arctica<\/span><span>. In general, Ichthysoporeans are characterized by having a thick cell wall, of uncknown composition, that is particularly hard to brake, making cell lysis difficult. Here we have introduce a simple modification on the conventional RNA extraction protocol using TRIzol reagent, by including two cycles of freezing-tawing of the cells-TRIzol suspension, in order to facilitate cell lysis. This modification improved significantly the RNA isolation yield. Total RNA is further treated with DNAse I enzyme and purified by precipitation to minimize genomic DNA contamination. Highly pure total RNA is then used to synthetize cDNA for downstream applications.<\/span><\/div><style>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t  .justify:after {\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t    content: \"\";\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t    display:inline-block;\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t    width: 100%;\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t  }\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/style><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><div class = \"justify\" style = \"text-align:justify\"><\/div><style>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t  .justify:after {\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t    content: \"\";\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t    display:inline-block;\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t    width: 100%;\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t  }\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/style><\/div><\/div>","changed_on":1550851563}